<title type="html"><![CDATA[12/31(Thu.) My philosophy for a happy life / Learning a language? Speak it like you’re playing a video game (Host:Cammy)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=458&amp;p=476#p476"><![CDATA[
<span style="color: #FF0000">Place:</span> 丹堤咖啡, 台北市延平南路107號2樓 (MRT 西門站4號出口)<br /><span style="color: #FF0000">Agenda:<br />6:30-</span>7:15 pm Free talk<br />7:15-7:50 pm Session 1 discussion<br />7:50-8:15 pm Presentation (At least two members of each table are invited, 2 mins / each member)<br />8:15-8:45 pm Session 2 discussion<br />8:45-<span style="color: #FF0000">9:00</span> pm Presentation<br /><br />Session I: My philosophy for a happy life<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=36m1o-tM05g&amp;feature=youtu.be">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=36m1o-t ... e=youtu.be</a><!-- m --><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sam_Berns">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sam_Berns</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Just before his passing on January 10, 2014, Sam Berns was a Junior at Foxboro High School in Foxboro, Massachusetts, where he achieved highest honors and was a percussion section leader in the high school marching band. He also achieved the rank of Eagle Scout in the Boy Scouts of America. Sam was diagnosed with Progeria, a rare, rapid aging disease, at the age of 2. Progeria, a rare disease, the premature aging disease include: tight skin, lack of weight gain, stunted growth, and heart disease. That affects an estimated 200 to 250 children worldwide.<br />He is featured in the Emmy award-winning documentary Life According to Sam, which premiered on HBO on October 21, 2013, 2 days before his 17th birthday.<br /><br />Questions:<br />Q1: This film mentioned that Sam got Progeria then John Hamilton asked Sam the question: “What is the most important thing that people should know about you?” And Sam’s answer was simply that I have a very happy life. Also, most of his time is spent thinking about things that have nothing to do with Progeria at all.<br />What do think about Sam’s philosophy? At the same time, share what you learned about the hard challenges of people with rare diseases<br />Q2: Referring to Sam’s speech, “the first aspect to his philosophy is that I’m okay with what I ultimately can’t do because there is so much I can do” … what do think his attitude? Also, please share your own experience about this philosophy.<br />Q3: Sam’s second philosophy is that I surround myself with people I want to be with, people of high quality. Do you agree or not? What kinds of people always support you throughout your life?<br />Q4: What methods do you often use to enable you to move forward quickly on bad day? Please share your tips or experience with table members<br />Q5: What’s your best learning from this lecture? How will you apply it to your future life?<br /><br />----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br />Session II: Learning a language? Speak it like you’re playing a video game<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ge7c7otG2mk&amp;feature=share">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ge7c7ot ... ture=share</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions:<br />Q1: How many years have you studied English? What bottlenecks have you encountered in the process of learning English? How did you overcome it?<br />Q2: From this TED video, the speaker, Marianna Pascal, shows how the secret to speaking a new language with confidence is all about attitude, not ability. Please share your comments or experiences.<br />Q3: Referring to this speech, &quot; English is not an art to be mastered, it's just a tool to use to get results &quot; Do you agree or not? Why?<br />Q4: Today is the end of this year. What are your expectations for learning English in the new year? How will you achieve it?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=25437">Michael</a> — Thu Dec 24, 2020 11:15 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
